    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between Makita LXT and XGT?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>LXT</strong> is Makita's 18V cordless platform with over 300 compatible tools — it's the world's largest cordless system and ideal for the vast majority of trade applications. <strong>XGT</strong> is the 40V max platform designed for the most demanding tools like SDS-MAX hammers, mitre saws and cut-off saws where 18V isn't enough. Both platforms have their own battery shape and charger.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are Makita LXT batteries compatible with XGT tools?",
            "answer": "<p>Not directly — LXT (18V) and XGT (40V) batteries have different shapes and voltages. However, Makita offers an <strong>adaptor (ADP10)</strong> that lets you use two LXT 18V batteries to power XGT 40V tools. This is a great way to transition to XGT without replacing all your batteries at once.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What does brushless mean and why does it matter?",
            "answer": "<p>Brushless motors use electronic commutation instead of carbon brushes, which means <strong>less friction, less heat and longer motor life</strong>. In practice, this gives you more power, more runtime per battery charge and a tool that lasts significantly longer. All professional-grade Makita tools now feature brushless motors.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is Makita's warranty on power tools?",
            "answer": "<p>All Makita power tools purchased from an authorised dealer carry a <strong>3-year manufacturer warranty</strong>. As an authorised Makita dealer, Invicta Tools can process warranty claims directly. We also stock a full range of genuine Makita spare parts and accessories.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Which Makita drill should I buy?",
            "answer": "<p>For most tradespeople, the <strong>LXT 18V brushless combi drill</strong> is the all-round choice — it drills, hammer drills and drives screws. If you need maximum power for large-diameter holes or heavy masonry, step up to the <strong>XGT 40V combi drill</strong>. For dedicated screw driving, the LXT impact driver is unbeatable.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Makita?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. As an authorised Makita dealer, we offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> on the full Makita range. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 210 459</strong> for bulk and trade account enquiries. We also offer free next-day delivery on orders over £30.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
